&lt;p&gt;The Electro-Optical Systems team at Planet is seeking an Opto-Mechanical Engineer to help drive the design of payloads in Planet’s fleet of Earth-imaging satellites. Your mission will be to champion our payload design efforts, with a specific focus on opto-mechanical design and manufacturing. The ideal candidate will be a seasoned opto-mechanical designer who has led optical system engineering efforts across multiple programs from conceptual design through flight. As a member of the Electro-Optical Systems team within Planet’s Space Systems division, you will be a key contributor and stakeholder in Planet’s agile aerospace approach to spacecraft design, and will work hand-in-glove with optical engineering, structural analysis, thermal engineering,&amp;nbsp; and reliability &amp;amp; qualification, as well as the rest of Planet’s leading-edge spacecraft design and manufacturing teams.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time, in-office position based in our San Francisco HQ 5 days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Impact You&#39;ll Own:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the opto-mechanical manufacturing process of optical payloads on Planet’s next-generation satellites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design the manufacturing line for mid-volume production of optical payloads. Make first principle based, data-driven decisions throughout the design process to ensure efficient assembly and test processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams such as structural, thermal analysts and optical engineer groups to drive and perform analyses to ensure payloads meet stiffness, strength, thermal, and launch survivability requirements, as well as maintain on-orbit performance through STOP (Structural, Thermal, Optical Performance)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive part and assembly design, manage fabrication with key vendors, perform failure analysis, and execute tolerance stackup and GD&amp;amp;T analyses to ensure precision and reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain comprehensive design documentation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technical presentations and reviews across all design review gates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support test planning and qualification test campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be hands-on with flight and test hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering, Aerospace Engineering, or a related technical field.&lt;
